5:
Finally cornered you! Now just hold
still—
10:
W-wait, I thought there was only one
suspect! Why didn't you warn me,
Clarita?!
14:
*yawn* Relax. There's only one
suspect. If there's anyone else there,
then...
21:
Alk, chase after him! I'll keep this
troubleshooter safe!
30:
Nice to meet you, Alk. I'm Clarita, a
PBC operator. My job is to provide
support to our heroes.
33: I've heard a lot about you.
36: Er, nice to meet you too?
38:
Hold on, how'd you get ahold of my
number? This isn't a company
communicator!
42:
You know cheap devices like yours
are easy to hack, right? You get
what you pay for.
45:
But never mind that. I'm not here for
a social call.
48:
You're never gonna nab that guy like
this. If there's one thing he's good at,
it's slipping away like the coward he
is.
55:
Just follow my lead, and he'll be ours
in no time.
61:
You've really gotta beef up your
security if you want to keep a hacker
like me out—
74: All your bots are belong to me.
78:
Honestly, I don't care about
punishing evil or any of that jazz...
82:
But you crossed the line when you
hurt my new coworker. See ya.
87:
I finished, Clarita! Can you check
this for me?
90:
Oh, this is looking good. Since you're
already a natural genius, it won't
take much training until you're
pulling your weight.
93:
Clarita, sorry to bug you, but can
you check something for me too?
101:
Wow, it's Alk in flesh bag form! Nice
to meet you in real life!
106:
I... feel like I should take offense to
that, but... Nice to see you too.
Thanks for helping out back there.
110:
Nah, I'm the one who should be
thanking you. Your friend made sure
my troubleshooter didn't get hurt.
113:
...I know you're from another world,
but still, you're pretty tough for an
organic.
116:
Oh, sorry, you want to keep this info
a secret, right?
124:
Ah, I didn't mean that to sound like a
threat. I'm just honestly interested.
127:
As an operator, I find myself
constantly analyzing other people's
capabilities and characteristics.
130:
Makes me wonder about people
from other worlds. How did you even
get here? I assume you also have a
way back?
133:
Most importantly, are all
otherworldly visitors friendly? Or just
you?
137:
Sounds like you want me to spill
everything.
142:
Well... Doesn't help that there's a
bunch of sketchy people popping
up lately.
144:
Who's to say you're the only ones
world-hopping? There could be
baddies sneaking their way in too.
146:
And if anything happens, it's my
troubleshooters that are gonna be
sent out to stop them.
149:
So you're asking me all this... to
protect the people here?
153:
I mean... That's part of it. This is the
only place that accepts a free spirit
like me.
155: I'd be in trouble if it ever went under.
159:
So... yeah. It's as much for them as it
is for me.
164:
When you put it that way, I don't
mind telling you what you want,
but... Where do I even begin...
169: How about you just show me?
173:
I'm not crazy about leaving my cozy
seat, but this seems like the best
way to go about it.
176:
Hey, everyone. Sorry about the
sudden notice, but I'm gonna be
using up my vacation days starting
tomorrow!
179:
H-huh?! I... I guess it's good that
you're finally using them, but...
182:
Ahaha, please. You'll be fine without
me for a bit.
185:
If anyone needs anything, my
handheld's good enough to provide
support. Now let's get this show on
the road!
